SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c04351097
Version: 1

HPSBMU03058 rev.1 - HP BladeSystem c-Class Onboard Administrator (OA) running
OpenSSL, Remote Disclosure of Information

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2014-06-25
Last Updated: 2014-06-25

Potential Security Impact: Remote disclosure of information

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company, HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified with HP BladeSystem
c-Class Onboard Administrator (OA) running OpenSSL. This vulnerability could
be exploited remotely to allow the disclosure of information.

References:

CVE-2014-0224 Remote Disclosure of Information
SSRT101591

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP BladeSystem c-Class Onboard Administrator (OA) 4.21 and earlier.

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2014-0224    (AV:N/AC:M/Au:N/C:P/I:P/A:P)       6.8
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

RESOLUTION

HP has made Onboard Administrator (OA) version 4.22 available to resolve this
vulnerability.

Go to
http://www.hp.com/go/oa

Select "Onboard Administrator Firmware"
Select ""HP BLc3000 Onboard Administrator Option" or "HP BLc7000 Onboard
Administrator Option"
Select the operating system from the list of choices
Select Firmware version 4.22 for download

HISTORY
Version:1 (rev.1) - 25 June 2014 Initial release

